column5: Kevin and I flew in to Eddie North's Camp at Windsor Lake.  On Saturday we unpacked and got the camp ready.  We only fished for four hours and got three pike in the low 40's.  Didn't get another big pike until Friday....we got two more in low 40's.  Monday night it rained for 27 hours.  Sunday through Thursday we caught hundreds of average size pike and walleye.   Overall we had a great trip.  Thanks Mike and Eddie.   Pike 42"  Small Pike were sure hungry  100's of Pikes caught like this  another big Pike  Kevin with a nice Walleye  That;s what 27"s of rain looks like!
nice report! thanks  I'm assuming you guys have been to Beteau. How you rate Windsor versus Beteau?
Nice pike, the top one has a cool pattern on it.
thanks chris we have not been to beteau we did stop there on the way out it looks nice
Nice fish! I have the fire tiger lure I see! That's a relief!
Nice all things worked out in the end Doug.  100's of fish with 40's to boot, the math all adds up. Good fishing dood.
Some nice pike for sure.   How long did it take you to bail the boat out??
thank's drew wish you were there. joey a lot of 5 gallon pail's
Glad it all worked out for you Doug! Windsor is an interesting body of water that few have had the opportunity to fish. One day I'll return myself...
